Class TestResults

java.lang.Object
com.example.TestResults
All Implemented Interfaces:
TestResultObserver
public class TestResults extends Object implements TestResultObserver
The TestResults class implements the TestResultObserver interface and serves as a container for storing and managing test results, including marks, feedback, and test names.

This class allows for updating test results via the update method and provides methods for retrieving the marks, feedback, and total marks. It also includes a toString method for displaying the stored test results in a readable format.
